---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_URL } from '../consts/site';
---

<Layout title="About Me" description="Learn more about Opik - Software engineer focused on modern web development, AI integration, and building with strong technical and business judgment.">
	<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
		"@context": "https://schema.org",
		"@type": "AboutPage",
		"name": "About Me",
		"description": "Learn more about Opik - Software engineer focused on modern web development, AI integration, and building with strong technical and business judgment.",
		"url": `${SITE_URL}/about`,
		"inLanguage": "en-US"
	})} />
	
	<article class="space-y-8">
		<header>
			<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tighter sm:text-4xl">About Me</h1>
		</header>
		
	<div class="prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert text-zinc-400 space-y-4 max-w-none">
		<p>
			I'm a relentless learner. I get genuinely excited understanding how things work,
			and most of all how businesses work: where they lose time, where they leave money
			on the table, and where a bit of technology would change everything.
		</p>

		<p>
			That makes me more than a builder. I'm the person you can sit down with to think
			through a problem, the analyst who spots the opportunity hiding in your process,
			and then the engineer who actually ships the fix, end to end. I've worked across
			many stacks, so I'm rarely boxed in by one tool.
		</p>

		<p>
			And I'm deeply into AI. To me it's close to a miracle for the programming world,
			and far beyond it. But I also know it isn't magic for its own sake. The value is
			in pointing it at the right problem, with judgment about what to automate, what to
			keep human, and what's actually worth shipping.
		</p>

		<p>
			AI already makes my own work faster and sharper. Most business owners haven't seen
			what it can do for them yet, and I'd love to help them find out.
		</p>

		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-50 pt-4">What I do</h2>
		<ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2.5">
			<li><strong class="text-zinc-50">Understand the business:</strong> map the process, find what's worth solving, and where tech actually pays off</li>
			<li><strong class="text-zinc-50">Build end to end:</strong> from architecture and design to a shipped, working product</li>
			<li><strong class="text-zinc-50">Apply AI with judgment:</strong> LLM integration and AI tooling aimed at real outcomes, not hype</li>
			<li><strong class="text-zinc-50">Work across the stack:</strong> React, Next.js, Vue, Nuxt, Astro, Tailwind, TypeScript, Node.js, REST APIs, Supabase, Prisma, WebSockets</li>
		</ul>

		<p class="pt-4">
			If you're a business owner curious about what AI and good engineering could do for
			you, or you just want to think a problem through, I'd be glad to talk.
		</p>
	</div>
	</article>
</Layout>
